==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*strǣlo-z'', from Indo-European ''*strē-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''strāla'', Middle Dutch ''strael'' (Dutch [[straal]]), Old High German ''strāla'' (German [[Strahl]]).  The IE root was also the source of Old Slavic ''strěla'' (Russian [[стрела]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'stræ:l/

===Noun===
'''strǣl''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''strǣlas''')
